{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:16:46.068946+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"issues\":[{\"number\":1,\"title\":\"Rate limit allows ~2x configured rate when bursting\",\"body\":\"---\\n\\nUpdate: I dug into bucket.lua more. I think the bug is line 25:\\n\\n    tokens = math.min(capacity, tokens + elapsed_sec * refill)\\n\\n`capacity` here is being read fresh from ARGV[1] on every call, so it\\ngets re-applied even after we\\u0026#39;ve already drawn the bucket down. Per\\nthe standard token-bucket spec the cap should only apply on the\\n*initial* fill, not on every refill recomputation, otherwise you get\\nthe over-rate behavior I\\u0026#39;m seeing.\\n\\nIf a maintainer can confirm this, happy to send a one-line patch that\\nmoves the `math.min(capacity, ...)` cap into the `tokens == nil`\\nbranch so it only fires when the bucket is initialized fresh. That\\nshould fix the example\\u0026#39;s 2x-overshoot without changing the documented\\nalgorithm.\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\"},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:05:02Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:05:06Z\"}],\"totalCount\":1,\"pageInfo\":{\"hasNextPage\":false,\"hasPreviousPage\":false,\"startCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowNTowMlrPAAAAAQwodP4=\",\"endCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowNTowMlrPAAAAAQwodP4=\"}}", "id": "lc_c7b4c964-8dac-471c-a59b-043c9b89ba5a"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "list_issues", "id": "b261ede4-d035-4f91-97e5-77da472b3cd3", "tool_call_id": "call_00_XcOe6hk8nake79cX6F6c5392", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
